#: ../../source/developers/deployment.rst:11
msgid ""
"We have written scripts to deploy Dataverse to Amazon Web Services (AWS) "
"but they require some setup."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developers/deployment.rst:14
msgid "Install AWS CLI"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developers/deployment.rst:16
msgid ""
"First, you need to have AWS Command Line Interface (AWS CLI) installed, "
"which is called ``aws`` in your terminal. Launching your terminal and "
"running the following command to print out the version of AWS CLI will "
"tell you if it is installed or not:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developers/deployment.rst:18
msgid "``aws --version``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developers/deployment.rst:20
msgid ""
"If you have not yet installed AWS CLI you should install it by following "
"the instructions at "
"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/userguide/installing.html"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developers/deployment.rst:22
msgid ""
"Afterwards, you should re-run the \"version\" command to verify that AWS "
"CLI has been properly installed. If \"version\" still doesn't work, read "
"on for troubleshooting advice. If \"version\" works, you can skip down to"
" the \"Configure AWS CLI\" step."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developers/deployment.rst:25
msgid "Troubleshooting \"aws: command not found\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developers/deployment.rst:27
msgid ""
"Please note that as of this writing the AWS docs are not especially clear"
" about how to fix errors such as ``aws: command not found``. If the AWS "
"CLI cannot be found after you followed the AWS installation docs, it is "
"very likely that the ``aws`` program is not in your ``$PATH``. ``$PATH`` "
"is an \"environment variable\" that tells your shell (usually Bash) where"
" to look for programs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developers/deployment.rst:29
msgid "To see what ``$PATH`` is set to, run the following command:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developers/deployment.rst:31
msgid "``echo $PATH``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developers/deployment.rst:33
msgid ""
"On Mac, to update your ``$PATH`` to include the location where the "
"current AWS docs install AWS CLI on the version of Python included with "
"your Mac, run the following command:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developers/deployment.rst:35
msgid "``export PATH=$PATH:$HOME/Library/Python/2.7/bin``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developers/deployment.rst:37
msgid "After all this, you can try the \"version\" command again."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developers/deployment.rst:39
msgid ""
"Note that it's possible to add an ``export`` command to your "
"``~/.bash_profile`` file so you don't have to run it yourself when you "
"open a new terminal."
msgstr ""

