msgid "Create a plain text file at ``~/.aws/config`` with the following content::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developers/deployment.rst:59
msgid ""
"Please note that at this time the region must be set to \"us-east-1\" but"
" in the future we could improve our scripts to support other regions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developers/deployment.rst:61
msgid ""
"Create a plain text file at ``~/.aws/credentials`` with the following "
"content::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developers/deployment.rst:67
msgid ""
"Then update the file and replace the values for \"aws_access_key_id\" and"
" \"aws_secret_access_key\" with your actual credentials by following the "
"instructions at https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/security/wheres-my-secret-"
"access-key/"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developers/deployment.rst:69
msgid ""
"If you are having trouble configuring the files manually, see "
"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/userguide/cli-chap-getting-"
"started.html which documents the ``aws configure`` command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developers/deployment.rst:74
msgid "Configure Ansible File (Optional)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developers/deployment.rst:76
msgid ""
"In order to configure Dataverse settings such as the password of the "
"dataverseAdmin user, download https://raw.githubusercontent.com/IQSS"
"/dataverse-ansible/master/defaults/main.yml and edit the file to your "
"liking."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developers/deployment.rst:78
msgid ""
"You can skip this step if you're fine with the values in the \"main.yml\""
" file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developers/deployment.rst:81
msgid "Download and Run the \"Create Instance\" Script"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developers/deployment.rst:83
msgid ""
"Once you have done the configuration, you are ready to try running the "
"\"create instance\" script to spin up Dataverse in AWS."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developers/deployment.rst:85
msgid ""
"Download :download:`ec2-create-instance.sh "
"<../../../../scripts/installer/ec2-create-instance.sh>` and put it "
"somewhere reasonable. For the purpose of these instructions we'll assume "
"it's in the \"Downloads\" directory in your home directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developers/deployment.rst:87
msgid ""
"You need to decide which branch you'd like to deploy to AWS. Select a "
"branch from https://github.com/IQSS/dataverse/branches/all such as "
"\"develop\" and pass it to the script with ``-b`` as in the following "
"example. (Branches such as \"master\" and \"develop\" are described in "
"the :doc:`version-control` section.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developers/deployment.rst:89
msgid "``bash ~/Downloads/ec2-create-instance.sh -b develop``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developers/deployment.rst:91
msgid ""
"You must specify the branch with ``-b`` but you can also specify a non-"
"IQSS git repo URL with ``-r`` as in the following example."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developers/deployment.rst:93
msgid ""
"``bash ~/Downloads/ec2-create-instance.sh -b develop -r "
"https://github.com/scholarsportal/dataverse.git``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developers/deployment.rst:95
msgid ""
"If you configured an Ansible file (:ref:`configure_ansible_file`) and "
"want to make use of it, add ``-g main.yml`` (or whatever you named your "
"file) as in the following example."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developers/deployment.rst:97
msgid ""
"``bash ~/Downloads/ec2-create-instance.sh -b develop -r "
"https://github.com/scholarsportal/dataverse.git -b main.yml``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developers/deployment.rst:99
msgid ""
"Now you will need to wait around 15 minutes until the deployment is "
"finished. Eventually, the output should tell you how to access the "
"installation of Dataverse in a web browser or via ssh. It will also "
"provide instructions on how to delete the instance when you are finished "
"with it. Please be aware that AWS charges per minute for a running "
"instance. You can also delete your instance from "
"https://console.aws.amazon.com/console/home?region=us-east-1 ."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developers/deployment.rst:102
msgid "Caveats"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developers/deployment.rst:104
msgid ""
"Please note that while the script should work fine on newish branches, "
"older branches that have different dependencies such as an older version "
"of Solr are now expected to yield a working Dataverse installation. Your "
"mileage may vary."
msgstr ""

